# Run Signal on native Wayland (mirrors org.ferdium.Ferdium — both Electron).
# The old X11 forcing existed to hide a gap between native-Wayland CSD and the
# pop-shell border under GNOME/Mutter; that's dead under Hyprland, and on a
# fractional (1.2) monitor scale XWayland gets bitmap-upscaled → grainy text.
# Granting the wayland socket + ELECTRON_OZONE_PLATFORM_HINT=auto makes Electron
# render natively at the fractional scale (sharp). The nixGL LIBGL/GBM/LIBVA
# unset-environment workaround was X11/GLX-only — native Wayland dodges it, so
# it's dropped here (Ferdium never needed it either).
[Context]
sockets=wayland;

[Environment]
ELECTRON_OZONE_PLATFORM_HINT=auto
